# autopsy/

Session autopsy reports that analyze conversation patterns across multiple sessions, detect rule enforcement failures, identify memory gaps, and propose convention updates. Each report contains findings organized by violation severity, enforcement failures, and undocumented conventions.

## Files

- `20260404.md` -- Latest autopsy (14 sessions, 2026-03-05 to 2026-04-04); detrope false positives identified, "overall" usage analysis, no enforcement failures
- `20260220b.md` -- Verification run post-memory-update (12 sessions with 7 compactions); confirms 6 memory updates applied, same false positive findings as 20260220.md
- `20260220.md` -- First autopsy report (12 sessions, 2026-02-17 to 2026-02-20); identified 4 corrections, 2 memory gaps, 3 real banned violations among 84 total
